Enum-Klasse StatisticStrategy

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<StatisticStrategy>
org.com.model.enums.StatisticStrategy
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
Serializable, Comparable<StatisticStrategy>, Constable
public enum StatisticStrategy extends Enum<StatisticStrategy>
An enumeration representing different strategies for statistical analysis in the application.

Each strategy corresponds to a specific type of analysis that can be performed on the cinematic data, such as counting genres or calculating average ratings.

  • GENRE_COUNT_STRATEGY - Counts the number of cinematics per genre.
  • STATE_COUNT_STRATEGY - Counts the number of cinematics by their state (e.g., finished, watching, dropped).
  • TYPE_COUNT_STRATEGY - Counts the number of cinematics by their type (e.g., movie, anime, series).
  • ACTOR_RATING_STRATEGY - Analyzes the average ratings of cinematics based on actors.
  • GENRE_RATING_STRATEGY - Analyzes the average ratings per genre.
  • AVERAGE_RATING_STRATEGY - Calculates the overall average rating of cinematics.
Version:

Autor:
